Node MUST be installed

/****************************************************/
To install package.json dependencies:

npm install
/****************************************************/


/****************************************************/
To run the server: nodemon
Nodemon will automatically restart the server when ANY change in the code is made.
/****************************************************/

/****************************************************/
You should read this:
https://github.com/sequelize/express-example
https://github.com/waiyaki/postgres-express-node-tutorial
/****************************************************/


/****************************************************/
To commit without message:
git commit -a --allow-empty-message -m ''
/****************************************************/


Professionals levels:
1 - ADMIN
2 - Medico
=======
/****************************************************/
To create a new sql user:
mysql -u root -p
CREATE USER 'novousuario'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'password';
GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON * . * TO 'novousuario'@'localhost';
/****************************************************/

/****************************************************/
To execute sql script
mysql -u USER -p < script.sql (open terminal in the same path)
/****************************************************/

/****************************************************/
Install order
apt-get install mysql-server
apt-get install mysql-client
apt-get install nodejs
apt-get install npm

create mysqluser
create mysqldb
npm install
npm install -g nodemon
sudo ln -s /usr/bin/nodejs /usr/bin/node
npm install passport
nodemon
/****************************************************/


